                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> This will be a great change if they take it far enough, otherwise it really will just be a nerf to soloers.  When I say take it far enough what I mean is this:  Groups will have to urgently seek to fill that 6th slot.  I'm not expecting SOE to actually implement this effectively, but if they somehow manage to make people desperate to fill out a group this will be a great change.  I really think that will be the key.  If getting a group becomes as easy as logging on and putting up your LFG flag for 10 min, then I'll be happy as a pig in shit.  The key to all of this will be that a full non-traditional group will still need to be able to XP faster than a soloer.  Sorry if that rubs some of you die-hard soloers the wrong way, but the way I see it is like this:  I should make more XP if I'm willing to put up with the hassle of a group, and the game should offer enough of a reward to make me want to do that.<br /><br />My necromancer exists because of all the time I was spending LFG with my other characters.  I have grouped a lot as a necro as well, but the reason he was getting played in the first place was because I could not stand the LFG time on other chars.  I have all but quit playing EQ in the last few months, instead spending my time in the Planetside and SWG betas.  Those games certainly have their faults but I still bought PS the day it went live (although I doubt I'll buy SWG,) and the main reason I am enjoying those games is the ease of getting groups.  In PS, I've NEVER shouted that I was LFS (Looking for Squad) - all I've ever done was go wait around the dropship center until someone invites me and that's usually less than 5 minutes.  <br /><br />Joining a group should not mean a multi-hour commitment nor should it be something people only do when they have to.  Grouping is one of the key components of this game and should be something the playerbase actively seeks to do.  Nobody is taking away the choice not to group; hopefully this change will help make soloing something you choose to do, rather than do it because you have no choice BUT to solo.  I just hope they test the crap out of this first.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
