                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> My 2 cents. I'm a longtime player with alot of alts over 60,<br /><br />This is horeshit. I have a 61 shammy and mage too so its not like im biased towards the soloers.<br /><br />People, THINK about what SOE is doing here:<br />1) They are fundamentally changing the game. This is the BIGGEST change EQ has ever seen. And its not a small change.. its F'ING HUGE. a 80% bonus is unreal. Tier 1 pop zones had a 33% bonus. This is 2.5x that. Think about it.<br /><br />2) This WILL kill soloers. Necros will be a dead class, The trinity (or aoe see below) will be the only way to go. This is great if I play my shaman or mage, but really poor if I play my necro.<br /><br />3) This is a HORRIBLE way to balance risk/reward. EQ has always been a game where soloers took more risk and were rewarded with mroe exp. Now there is literally no reason to solo. The top exp zones will have thier exp cut. You will still have the same risk. You will be penalized if you dont group, because groups will be getting more exp than a soloer used to, at little to NO risk.<br /><br />Let me restate that. SOE is taking a system of high exp and high risk and morphing it to one of high exp and no risk... if you are one of the "grouping classes".<br /><br />4) SOE has not stated it, but logic dictates they are doing it for LoY and upcoming expansions. Think about it. They realized the huge exp bonus in PoP was a mistake from a marketing standpoint. They cant keep rolling out expansions with higher and higher exp bonuses. LoY has lower exp bonuses than pop. People play in PoP instead of LoY zones because of this. They same with new expansions when they come out. But cutting PoP exp, SOE will move players into LoY and other expansion zones. If you get the same exp off of a lvl 53 mob in PoP or in LoY, but the LoY mob also drops plat/loot, why the hell are you gonna stay in PoP.<br /><br />5) There is HUGE potential for abuse here. The AOE groups will be the ultimate exp king. When you lower the blues down to 50 for a 65, nerf the pop exp modifier, and then add in a HUGE % for a full group, the BEST way to make exp is to take 4 wizards, 1 tank, and a cleric to a zone that has gobs of lvl 48-52 mobs. Pull 10 or 20 of them, aoe them to death, and you are gonna get INSANE exp with the bonus. I'm talking INSANE. do the math. There will be little or no risk here cause 4 wizzards will kill them in one shot. You could keep this up forever.<br /><br />I can think of 2 other ways to exploit this beyond belief. BTW there is no way to "FIX" the above exploit. ITs fundamentally built into the exp change.<br /><br />In sumary, before everyone heralds this as "a much needed change" Think about it. I mean REALLY think about it. It hurts 3 classes pretty bad. It helps the other classes to some extent. 4 classes it helps alot, and one of those classes (wizards) are going to be exp machines. You thought chanters charming was insane, wait till you see what a wizard group can do with this.<br /><br />The reality is SOE has NOT thought this out. I'm pretty confident it wont go live as stated on test, but a watered down version will. Still, its going to hurt soloers and reward grouping. That HURTS the casual player and rewards the hard core player. It will push people to alternate games like WoW. Before this announcement i had no interest in WoW. Now im midly interested. AND I HAVE 60+ CLASSES THAT BENEFIT FROM THIS. I cant imagine the poor guy thats poured a year or 2 of time into only 1 or 2 solo classes.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
