                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" height="100%" width="100%" colspan="2" valign="top"><a name="168963"></a>
                  <table width="100%" height="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td colspan="2" valign="top">
                      <img src="images/icon_mi_1.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" hspace="3" /><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/28/2003&nbsp;:&nbsp; 10:09:55 AM</font>
                      &nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=574"><img src="images/icon_profile.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Show Profile" title="Show Profile" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=168963&TOPIC_ID=18520&FORUM_ID=2"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Even though I should know better than to answer to a troll, I'll do it this one time:<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">All I can say is thank GOD this is being done...SOLOING IS OVER POWERED...for all you whiny-namby-pamby-i-want-to-level-to-65-in-14-hours necromancers can just suffer like the clerics have for years...this is good for the game.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Screwing up a player-subset's xp system is NOT good for the game. The only thing that will do is to spread the misery that dumbasses like you have been causing for years by incessant moaning. If group xp has been crap, it's mostly because fuckwits like you spend more time looking at the soloers than concentrating on making your group more xp.<br /><br />/flame off<br /><br />Having got that off my chest, group xp should've been higher from the start of the game, not 5 years later. To me, it makes more sense that a player should get xp at the same rate while killing the same mobs, regardless of whether he/she is grouped or solo. So if A gains Y xp in an hour killing lots of mob D in a group, player B should also get Y xp in an hour killing lots of mob D solo. Soloing has its difficulties and benefits, so does grouping. So to say that one method of xping is merits more xp than the other is baseless.<br /><br />As opposed to nerfing solo xp. It doesn't matter that it's only going to be in PoP because that's still where most of us 61+ will do our hardcore xp. The old world zones, regardless of the extension of the xp range, will still give drastically less xp because you will no longer be fighting stuff that's around your level. A level 52 mob will still give less xp than a level 62 mob.<br /><br />Necros don't have as many problems getting groups these days. However, the problem isn't finding a group that recognizes our killing power, the problem is finding a group that actually has space. The majority of players in the game have, whether by luck or design or time limitations, ended up playing solo classes. Yes, it is possible for solo classes to group up. But most times you are very limited in where you can go, what you can kill and how many mobs are available for killing. In addition, you can't just head off to separate corners off the zone to kill mobs on your own because xp doesn't get split if you are too far from the rest of your group.<br /><br />The only other thing I can say is that I'm glad that I'm 65 now and that there isn't any xp penalty for AA. Because as an Iksar who pretty much grouped all the way up to 65, I'd always had to add in some extra soloing time just to keep up with my friends. Reducing solo xp would've greatly increased the time it took me to get to 65, even if it was only in the PoP zones. My commiserations to all up-and-coming Iksar necros out there, this change will truly suck and I advise you to level as much as possible before the change goes live.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
